value: London : Printed for and sold by I. Walsh, [approximately 1745]

The overture, 12 arias and 1 duet selected from various earlier publications.
Title added in manuscript to a Collins frame (see W.C. Smith).
Italian words.
Staff notation.
Copy notes
Founder's bequest, 1816. Inscribed on page 1: "R. Fitzwilliam, 1767". 
Received stab stitched in paper covers. Bound in quarter Morocco leather Cockerell paper sides and vellum tips by the Cockerell Bindery in March, 1981. 
Lacking title page: title "Lotharius" written in manuscript on cover. 
Recorded in W.C. Smith as no. 8 (ca. 1760, another issue of no. 7). 
Publisher number : No. 619 Walsh
Former shelf numbers: 31.F.14 & x.2.54(a). UkCU-FWM
